5. Gap Analysis (Current State → Future State)
5.1 Asset Management (AM)
Current State
No unified asset inventory

OT devices tracked manually in spreadsheets

Shadow IT discovered at two remote sites

No lifecycle management process

NESA IAS Requirement
Maintain a centralized, accurate, continuously updated asset inventory

Classify assets based on criticality

Track ownership and lifecycle

Gap Severity: High
Future State
Deploy automated asset discovery tools

Integrate IT + OT inventories

Assign asset owners

Implement quarterly reconciliation

5.2 Physical Security (PS)
Current State
Two substations use shared access cards

No CCTV coverage for server room

Visitor logs maintained manually and inconsistently

No tamper‑evident seals on OT cabinets

NESA IAS Requirement
Unique access credentials

CCTV monitoring for critical areas

Visitor access logging

Physical tamper protection

Gap Severity: High
Future State
Implement unique card access

Install CCTV with 90‑day retention

Digitize visitor logs

Add tamper‑evident seals and periodic inspections

5.3 Access Control (AC)
Current State
Privileged accounts shared among engineers

No MFA for remote access

No quarterly access reviews

Password policy outdated (8 characters, no rotation)

NESA IAS Requirement
Unique privileged accounts

MFA for all remote access

Quarterly access reviews

Strong password policy

Gap Severity: Critical
Future State
Enforce MFA

Eliminate shared accounts

Implement IAM governance

Update password policy to NESA standards

5.4 Incident Response (IR)
Current State
No formal incident response plan

No defined severity levels

No evidence of tabletop exercises

Logs retained for only 14 days

NESA IAS Requirement
Documented IR plan

Defined severity classification

Regular IR exercises

Log retention aligned with NESA (minimum 90 days)

Gap Severity: High
Future State
Develop IR plan with roles and escalation paths

Conduct quarterly tabletop exercises

Extend log retention to 90+ days

Integrate logs with SIEM

5.5 Business Continuity (BC)
Current State
No tested disaster recovery plan

Backups stored in same region as primary systems

No RTO/RPO defined

No redundancy for pipeline monitoring system

NESA IAS Requirement
Documented and tested BC/DR plans

Offsite backups

Defined RTO/RPO

Redundancy for critical OT systems

Gap Severity: High
Future State
Establish offsite backup strategy

Define RTO/RPO

Implement redundant monitoring nodes

Conduct annual BC/DR tests

